WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.519
Bible there with you, Psalm 25, and last week we started a little mini-series, just a three-part

00:00:06.519 --> 00:00:14.399
series here going through Psalm 25 and having the opportunity, as we finished up a couple

00:00:14.399 --> 00:00:20.520
of weeks ago, the study on the names of God, and it's just a blessing to walk through

00:00:20.520 --> 00:00:21.520
the Psalms.

00:00:21.520 --> 00:00:27.559
I'm so thankful for the book of Psalms, and it's such a source of encouragement,

00:00:27.559 --> 00:00:34.119
and the psalmist is so transparent, and we can relate to, and we can get help from.

00:00:34.119 --> 00:00:38.840
Of course, all of God's Word is profitable, and we're thankful for every part of it

00:00:38.840 --> 00:00:40.080
this evening.

00:00:40.080 --> 00:00:45.159
As we continue through the Psalm, let me just do a quick reminder of what we looked at last

00:00:45.159 --> 00:00:50.159
week in the first few verses, David, it's the Psalm of David, and he begins the Psalm

00:00:50.159 --> 00:00:51.159
this way,

00:00:51.159 --> 00:01:14.760
As we looked last week at this Psalm, and we looked at the first three verses, and then

00:01:14.760 --> 00:01:20.199
several verses throughout the Psalm, we spoke about the fact that the psalmist was longing

00:01:20.239 --> 00:01:21.559
for peace.

00:01:21.559 --> 00:01:26.319
He was longing for peace, and there were some things that David was facing in his life,

00:01:26.319 --> 00:01:32.080
some circumstances that were adverse, and he was dealing with this great time of difficulty,

00:01:32.080 --> 00:01:38.559
and these circumstances drove him to his knees, it caused him to lift up his soul to the Lord,

00:01:38.559 --> 00:01:44.040
to seek the Lord, and in the time of difficulty, when he was needing peace, because of all

00:01:44.040 --> 00:01:51.400
of the chaos and the turmoil that was around him, he knew that he could go to Jehovah Shalom,

00:01:51.400 --> 00:01:58.199
the God who is our peace, and what a blessing to understand that, and at times, in the midst

00:01:58.199 --> 00:02:03.199
of our storms, in the midst of the storms of those that have gone before us, we need

00:02:03.199 --> 00:02:09.960
today, we need for our Savior, who is the Prince of Peace, to stand and say, peace,

00:02:09.960 --> 00:02:10.960
be still.

00:02:10.960 --> 00:02:12.800
And aren't you thankful that He can do that?

00:02:12.800 --> 00:02:18.240
I'm so thankful that in the midst of all sorts of chaos and turmoil, and we live in

00:02:18.240 --> 00:02:26.080
a tumultuous time, we live with all sorts of things that we face personally and corporately,

00:02:26.080 --> 00:02:32.479
and we see those things, and we find that in a time of great chaos, that we can go to

00:02:32.479 --> 00:02:36.039
the Lord and seek Him for that peace.

00:02:36.039 --> 00:02:41.360
As we continue looking through this Psalm, we note number two, and it's the lesson for

00:02:41.360 --> 00:02:47.919
this evening, that not only was David having a longing for peace, but we find throughout

00:02:47.919 --> 00:02:51.600
the Psalm here that there's a longing for direction.

00:02:51.600 --> 00:02:53.500
There's a longing for direction.

00:02:53.500 --> 00:02:58.380
No doubt in your life, and in my life as well, there are times in which we have much chaos

00:02:58.380 --> 00:03:04.399
going on, and we need peace, and we know that we can go to God and He can give peace, but

00:03:04.399 --> 00:03:11.720
then at other times, we are facing circumstances and difficulties, and we just need direction.

00:03:11.720 --> 00:03:15.559
Have you ever been in a position where you just don't know what to do?

00:03:15.559 --> 00:03:17.839
Just don't know what to do.

00:03:17.839 --> 00:03:23.279
And the truth of the matter is that we are not omniscient.

00:03:23.279 --> 00:03:25.440
Amen?

00:03:25.440 --> 00:03:30.399
The Bible talks about the prudent man, and we're to be prudent, to try to see those things

00:03:30.399 --> 00:03:35.600
ahead, but the reality is that we don't know what's on tomorrow, but God does.

00:03:35.600 --> 00:03:38.759
How many of you use GPS?

00:03:38.759 --> 00:03:41.960
How many of you have a map in your car, the old Rand McNally?

00:03:41.960 --> 00:03:42.960
Any of you got that?

00:03:42.960 --> 00:03:43.960
A couple of you.

00:03:43.960 --> 00:03:44.960
Praise the Lord.

00:03:44.960 --> 00:03:47.759
Y'all are prepared, amen?

00:03:47.759 --> 00:03:49.440
And still use it, right?

00:03:49.440 --> 00:03:50.440
Why?

00:03:50.440 --> 00:03:53.000
Because sometimes that GPS might fail you.

00:03:53.000 --> 00:03:54.960
Holly was trying to get back to the church.

00:03:54.960 --> 00:03:58.880
We had a, there was a board meeting in the afternoon at that beacon rally, and I was

00:03:58.880 --> 00:04:01.960
part of that, and so she wasn't there for that, and she was trying to make her way back

00:04:01.960 --> 00:04:07.520
to the church, and the reception wasn't so great, and the GPS said, you have reached

00:04:07.520 --> 00:04:11.639
your destination, you may have to walk.

00:04:11.639 --> 00:04:14.559
I'd never heard a GPS say that before.

00:04:14.559 --> 00:04:17.920
And let me just tell you, she would have had to walk for an hour or more from where she

00:04:17.920 --> 00:04:20.320
was to be where the church was.

00:04:20.320 --> 00:04:22.279
It took her completely to the wrong place.

00:04:22.279 --> 00:04:26.279
She called me, and I said, honey, I have no idea where you are.

00:04:26.279 --> 00:04:30.320
So with having no idea where you are, and honestly, even if I knew where she was, I

00:04:30.320 --> 00:04:34.679
don't know that I would know how to get her to where I was, because I'm not familiar with

00:04:34.679 --> 00:04:35.679
that area.

00:04:35.679 --> 00:04:36.679
You know what she needed?

00:04:36.679 --> 00:04:38.559
She needed some direction.

00:04:38.559 --> 00:04:39.559
And so Bart, guess what I did?

00:04:39.559 --> 00:04:43.040
It was 6.58, church started at 7 o'clock, I was stressed out, how am I gonna get my

00:04:43.040 --> 00:04:47.399
wife here, I don't know how to help her, and I thought, Donna Stroop is here.

00:04:47.399 --> 00:04:50.239
Now some of you guys know Dan Stroop, Donna Stroop, they lived there, they lived there

00:04:50.239 --> 00:04:51.239
for years.

00:04:51.239 --> 00:04:54.839
I said, Donna will be able to talk her through how to get here.

00:04:54.839 --> 00:04:58.880
And I went and found Donna, and I said, Donna, can you please call Holly?

00:04:58.880 --> 00:04:59.880
She's lost.

00:04:59.880 --> 00:05:02.119
Can you help her get here?

00:05:02.119 --> 00:05:03.119
You know what?

00:05:03.119 --> 00:05:07.480
She was able to one step at a time, she needed direction.

00:05:07.480 --> 00:05:10.600
But I couldn't give it to her.

00:05:10.600 --> 00:05:16.559
But there was somebody that could, and if I could use that physical illustration of

00:05:16.559 --> 00:05:22.519
an event that took place just last night, in your life and in my life, we need direction,

00:05:22.519 --> 00:05:24.720
we need God's direction.

00:05:24.799 --> 00:05:27.720
We need God to provide us with leadership.

00:05:27.720 --> 00:05:34.279
And as we look at this passage of Scripture, and we note the approach of David, I would

00:05:34.279 --> 00:05:39.959
say that David's approach here in Psalm 25 when he's longing for direction, when he's

00:05:39.959 --> 00:05:44.040
seeking the Lord, that his approach is exemplary.

00:05:44.040 --> 00:05:48.399
And it's noteworthy that we would take and we would look at this and we would learn from

00:05:48.399 --> 00:05:54.679
this and not only understand that David was making good decisions and David was following

00:05:54.679 --> 00:06:00.320
a good path, but this is not just provided for us to be able to look at a historical

00:06:00.320 --> 00:06:05.179
account, but so that we could learn that in our lives we need direction and we can go

00:06:05.179 --> 00:06:09.959
to God knowing that He can provide that direction for us.

00:06:09.959 --> 00:06:15.140
In fact, just this week I sent a text message to one of the young people in our church,

00:06:15.140 --> 00:06:18.839
and I sent a text message just letting them know I was praying for them, how school was,

00:06:18.839 --> 00:06:22.799
so on and so forth, and I said, listen, is there anything specific I can pray for you

00:06:22.799 --> 00:06:24.000
about?

00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:28.519
And they sent me a text back and they didn't say these words, would you pray for direction,

00:06:28.519 --> 00:06:32.339
but through everything that they said in the text message, basically if you boiled it down

00:06:32.339 --> 00:06:36.079
into a single statement, it was, would you pray for direction?

00:06:36.079 --> 00:06:39.440
And I'm thankful that God will answer that prayer.

00:06:39.440 --> 00:06:41.559
Notice with me the example of David here.

00:06:41.559 --> 00:06:47.679
Notice his behavior, what he does in a time of needing direction, longing for direction.

00:06:47.679 --> 00:06:55.880
In verse number four, he says, show me thy ways, O Lord.

00:06:55.880 --> 00:07:01.239
Notice where he says, show me thy ways, O Lord.

00:07:01.239 --> 00:07:08.160
And David is interested in having direction, but he's interested in having divine direction.

00:07:08.160 --> 00:07:15.040
He's interested in God showing, revealing to him, teaching him God's ways.

00:07:15.040 --> 00:07:22.079
He says, teach me, notice in verse number four, teach me thy paths.

00:07:22.079 --> 00:07:28.359
And we notice that as David says in verse number four, show me and teach me, he's seeking

00:07:28.359 --> 00:07:34.100
the Lord, the one who is Jehovah God, the one who knows all things, the one who knows

00:07:34.100 --> 00:07:39.239
what's on the morrow, and he needs direction, he's longing for direction, and so he says,

00:07:39.239 --> 00:07:42.440
show me thy ways, teach me thy paths.

00:07:42.440 --> 00:07:50.239
And then we find in verse number five, he says, lead me in thy truth, and teach me,

00:07:50.239 --> 00:07:58.320
for thou art the God of my salvation, on thee do I wait all the day.

00:07:58.320 --> 00:08:00.600
Isn't that a great approach?

00:08:00.600 --> 00:08:05.799
When someone is longing for direction, when David, if it is in fact the case that he's

00:08:05.799 --> 00:08:11.640
dealing with the revolt of Absalom, as many assume to be the setting for this particular

00:08:11.640 --> 00:08:17.040
psalm, and he has all of this chaos in the kingdom and all these things that are going

00:08:17.040 --> 00:08:20.160
on, and God, what do I do?

00:08:20.160 --> 00:08:21.720
How do I handle this?

00:08:21.720 --> 00:08:23.920
What step do I take?

00:08:23.920 --> 00:08:31.640
And notice he says, for thou art the God of my salvation, and then he says this, on thee

00:08:31.640 --> 00:08:33.679
do I wait all the day.

00:08:33.679 --> 00:08:41.919
He had mentioned earlier in verse number three about yea, let none that wait on thee be ashamed,

00:08:41.919 --> 00:08:46.400
and we mentioned last week, and it's worth repeating this evening, that this idea of

00:08:46.400 --> 00:08:52.840
waiting is not only patiently waiting for the Lord to provide and to give the green

00:08:52.840 --> 00:08:58.760
light, so to speak, with regard to the direction, but there's also the idea of serving the Lord,

00:08:58.760 --> 00:09:03.919
waiting on the Lord, and both are seen within even the passage.

00:09:03.919 --> 00:09:09.679
When I'm waiting on God to provide me for direction for my next step, I continue to

00:09:09.679 --> 00:09:11.520
serve the Lord.

00:09:11.520 --> 00:09:16.520
I don't stop serving God because I'm waiting for the next piece of information, or the

00:09:16.520 --> 00:09:22.760
next step that I'm to take, no, I'm actively doing what I know that God has already told

00:09:22.760 --> 00:09:27.960
me to do as I'm waiting for direction in that next step.

00:09:27.960 --> 00:09:33.599
And we find that David here, he says teach me, he says it in verse number four, he says

00:09:33.599 --> 00:09:38.719
it again in verse number five, can I tell you this evening that just in those simple

00:09:38.719 --> 00:09:48.640
words it reveals to us something that is important, humility, humility.

00:09:48.640 --> 00:09:57.679
You know, to be taught requires humility, and when we think about David saying here,

00:09:57.679 --> 00:09:59.760
to the Lord, teach me.

00:09:59.760 --> 00:10:03.400
David knows that God is far greater than he is,

00:10:03.400 --> 00:10:06.240
and so he's going to have this humble approach.

00:10:06.240 --> 00:10:08.400
It reveals to us not only humility,

00:10:08.400 --> 00:10:10.280
but it reveals to us dependence.

00:10:10.280 --> 00:10:11.320
Teach me.

00:10:12.380 --> 00:10:14.480
Lord, I'm depending on you.

00:10:14.480 --> 00:10:16.720
I'm trusting you, Lord.

00:10:16.720 --> 00:10:19.580
I don't know what to do.

00:10:20.480 --> 00:10:21.720
Teach me.

00:10:21.720 --> 00:10:23.280
I'm gonna be humble.

00:10:23.280 --> 00:10:24.800
I'm gonna wait.

00:10:24.800 --> 00:10:25.880
I'm gonna be dependent.

00:10:25.880 --> 00:10:30.240
And I'm gonna recognize that you are the one

00:10:30.240 --> 00:10:34.520
that is able to provide me with the direction that I need,

00:10:34.520 --> 00:10:37.820
and I desperately need direction.

00:10:37.820 --> 00:10:40.540
Notice, if you will, as we continue to look at this

00:10:40.540 --> 00:10:43.060
throughout the psalm as we did last week

00:10:43.060 --> 00:10:46.460
and looked at various aspects of the longing for peace,

00:10:46.460 --> 00:10:48.480
but even this longing for direction.

00:10:48.480 --> 00:10:50.640
Notice, if you will, in verse number eight.

00:10:51.800 --> 00:10:53.820
Good and upright is the Lord.

00:10:53.820 --> 00:10:55.220
Isn't that a great statement?

00:10:55.220 --> 00:10:57.400
Listen, our God is good all the time.

00:10:57.400 --> 00:11:00.240
God is good because that's who he is.

00:11:00.240 --> 00:11:03.120
It's not based upon your circumstances or my circumstances.

00:11:03.120 --> 00:11:05.160
God is good.

00:11:05.160 --> 00:11:07.040
He's good all the time.

00:11:07.040 --> 00:11:09.040
And then he says, therefore,

00:11:09.040 --> 00:11:11.200
because God is good and upright,

00:11:11.200 --> 00:11:16.200
therefore will he teach sinners in the way.

00:11:16.720 --> 00:11:17.960
Now, think about the fact,

00:11:17.960 --> 00:11:21.440
if we could look at this and understand this this evening,

00:11:21.440 --> 00:11:25.300
who we are in relationship to who he is.

00:11:25.300 --> 00:11:28.900
Now, I'm thankful this evening because of salvation.

00:11:28.900 --> 00:11:30.660
I am a child of God.

00:11:30.660 --> 00:11:33.020
I'm a joint heir with Jesus Christ.

00:11:33.020 --> 00:11:35.540
I have been adopted, hallelujah.

00:11:35.540 --> 00:11:39.860
I am his son and praise God for that.

00:11:39.860 --> 00:11:42.620
But the God of the universe that would save us,

00:11:42.620 --> 00:11:44.240
that knows everything about us,

00:11:44.240 --> 00:11:49.240
that he would care enough about our lives

00:11:49.240 --> 00:11:51.740
to provide us with direction,

00:11:52.660 --> 00:11:57.660
that he would take interest in each of us as individuals

00:11:57.860 --> 00:11:59.500
and provide us with direction.

00:11:59.500 --> 00:12:04.100
It's amazing that God loves us that much.

00:12:04.100 --> 00:12:05.940
God didn't save us and then just say,

00:12:05.940 --> 00:12:07.240
figure it out for yourselves.

00:12:07.240 --> 00:12:10.140
God didn't create and say, you guys all figured out.

00:12:10.140 --> 00:12:14.700
No, God has a personal interest in every single one of us.

00:12:14.700 --> 00:12:17.300
And the truth of the matter this evening

00:12:17.300 --> 00:12:19.800
is that all of us need direction,

00:12:19.800 --> 00:12:22.400
but all of us need different direction.

00:12:22.400 --> 00:12:23.320
Why do I say that?

00:12:23.320 --> 00:12:26.320
Because we're all dealing with different things.

00:12:26.320 --> 00:12:28.220
And we need direction in our lives

00:12:28.220 --> 00:12:29.660
for the things that we're facing

00:12:29.660 --> 00:12:31.600
and the direction that I need

00:12:31.600 --> 00:12:33.920
is different than the direction that you need.

00:12:33.920 --> 00:12:35.320
And the direction that you need

00:12:35.320 --> 00:12:37.380
is different than the direction that someone else needs.

00:12:37.380 --> 00:12:38.220
Why?

00:12:38.220 --> 00:12:39.040
Because you're dealing

00:12:39.040 --> 00:12:41.400
with a different set of circumstances.

00:12:43.160 --> 00:12:46.640
We understand that as we are facing the circumstances

00:12:46.700 --> 00:12:50.260
in life and as we go to God and we seek him.

00:12:50.260 --> 00:12:54.060
Listen, I find this evening that how does God teach us?

00:12:54.060 --> 00:12:56.180
He teaches us through his word.

00:12:57.100 --> 00:12:59.700
So we can't simply say, Lord, teach me

00:12:59.700 --> 00:13:02.920
and then have no relationship to his word.

00:13:02.920 --> 00:13:04.660
We can't say, Lord, teach me

00:13:04.660 --> 00:13:08.060
and then skip out on going to hearing the public teaching

00:13:08.060 --> 00:13:09.380
and preaching of God's word.

00:13:09.380 --> 00:13:10.200
Why?

00:13:10.200 --> 00:13:14.180
Because God's gonna use his word to give us an answer

00:13:14.180 --> 00:13:17.000
to the prayer of seeking direction.

00:13:17.000 --> 00:13:20.100
We can't skip our Bible reading.

00:13:20.100 --> 00:13:20.940
Why?

00:13:20.940 --> 00:13:23.040
Because God's gonna provide that direction.

00:13:23.040 --> 00:13:26.080
Thy word is a lamp unto my feet.

00:13:26.080 --> 00:13:28.440
Is that not what the Bible says of itself?

00:13:28.440 --> 00:13:31.040
And God will provide that direction.

00:13:31.040 --> 00:13:34.120
Not only does God use his word to give us direction,

00:13:34.120 --> 00:13:36.400
but God uses the Holy Spirit.

00:13:36.400 --> 00:13:38.280
And I'm thankful for the Holy Spirit.

00:13:38.280 --> 00:13:42.120
I'm thankful that at the moment of salvation,

00:13:42.120 --> 00:13:45.380
we are indwelled with the Spirit of God.

00:13:45.380 --> 00:13:47.360
And the Spirit of God will guide us.

00:13:47.360 --> 00:13:50.300
He will teach us and he will guide us into all truth.

00:13:50.300 --> 00:13:51.780
But I want you to understand something

00:13:51.780 --> 00:13:53.940
extremely important this evening.

00:13:53.940 --> 00:13:58.740
The Holy Spirit of God will never lead the child of God

00:13:58.740 --> 00:14:02.100
to do something contrary to the word of God.

00:14:03.580 --> 00:14:07.180
The Holy Spirit of God will always,

00:14:08.120 --> 00:14:12.520
every single time, he will always lead us,

00:14:12.520 --> 00:14:17.559
direct us in agreement with his written word.

00:14:17.559 --> 00:14:19.160
It's important for us to understand why.

00:14:19.160 --> 00:14:20.640
Because sometimes people take a step back and say,

00:14:20.640 --> 00:14:22.460
well, the Spirit led me.

00:14:22.460 --> 00:14:23.720
No, no, no, no, no.

00:14:23.720 --> 00:14:25.520
I'm not sure what spirit that was,

00:14:25.520 --> 00:14:28.279
but John says try the spirits.

00:14:28.279 --> 00:14:29.360
Does he not?

00:14:30.880 --> 00:14:35.800
And we find here this evening that David is understanding

00:14:35.820 --> 00:14:38.300
that because of God's character,

00:14:38.300 --> 00:14:40.100
that is noted here in verse number eight,

00:14:40.100 --> 00:14:43.700
that he was confident that God will teach.

00:14:43.700 --> 00:14:47.300
Therefore, will he teach sinners in the way?

00:14:47.300 --> 00:14:51.040
And what a joy to know that God will provide us

00:14:51.040 --> 00:14:54.760
when we come to him and say, God, I need direction.

00:14:55.860 --> 00:14:57.260
He says, okay.

00:14:57.260 --> 00:14:59.460
Now, here's the important thing.

00:14:59.460 --> 00:15:00.300
We gotta also determine

00:15:00.300 --> 00:15:02.200
that we're gonna follow his direction.

00:15:03.260 --> 00:15:04.100
Amen?

00:15:05.040 --> 00:15:08.000
When we ask for God's direction,

00:15:08.000 --> 00:15:10.320
when we seek the Lord and we say,

00:15:10.320 --> 00:15:13.920
Lord, guide us, lead us, show us,

00:15:13.920 --> 00:15:16.520
we must come, we must approach that

00:15:16.520 --> 00:15:20.800
with the heart attitude of obedience.

00:15:20.800 --> 00:15:23.320
It's like Samuel when he says,

00:15:23.320 --> 00:15:26.000
speak, Lord, for thy servant heareth.

00:15:27.200 --> 00:15:30.760
That word hereth carries with it the idea

00:15:30.760 --> 00:15:33.559
of I'm going to hear it so that I can do it,

00:15:33.580 --> 00:15:35.820
so that I can carry it out.

00:15:35.820 --> 00:15:38.420
That's what the word means.

00:15:38.420 --> 00:15:40.860
And so when I seek God for direction,

00:15:40.860 --> 00:15:43.920
when you seek God for direction and God answers,

00:15:43.920 --> 00:15:45.779
it's not that I say, okay, now I'm gonna consider

00:15:45.779 --> 00:15:48.500
if I'm gonna follow this direction or not.

00:15:48.500 --> 00:15:50.180
